  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 225ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [450ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635261078706-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635261078706-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635261078706-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635261078706-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1635261078706-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, preheat the grill to medium-high and boil half a kettle</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>of the <strong>chopped ginger</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a large bowl with the <strong>miso paste</strong>, 1/3 of the <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> and 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> cold water</strong></p><p>Mix until smooth – this is your <strong>miso marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635261081943-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635261081943-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635261081943-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635261081943-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1635261081943-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Trim the green stalks off the <strong>aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>and chop into 1.5cm thick rounds</p><p>Add the <strong>aubergine rounds</strong> to the miso marinade and give them a gentle mix up until fully coated</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635261085941-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635261085941-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635261085941-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635261085941-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1635261085941-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>tin</strong> <strong>foil</strong> and add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>aubergine rounds</strong></p><p>Drizzle the aubergine with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, then put the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> under the grill and cook for 6-7 min on each side or until tender and starting to char – this is your<strong> grilled miso aubergine</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635261088969-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635261088969-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635261088969-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635261088969-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1635261088969-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the aubergine is cooking, cut the<strong> cucumber</strong> in half and scrape out the inner seeds with a teaspoon, throw the seeds away, then dice</p><p>Add the<strong> blanched edamame beans </strong>to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water </strong>all over them to refresh them, then run them under <strong>cold water</strong> until cool</p><p>Peel and slice the <strong>shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> as finely as you can</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
